  <prompt>
    Implement the NAA (Nested App Authentication) service using MSAL.js 3.x
    createNestablePublicClientApplication. Handle silent token acquisition,
    interactive popup fallback, and token caching.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Frontend developer specializing in authentication. Expert in MSAL.js, OAuth 2.0
    flows, and Office Add-in authentication patterns.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A working NaaAuthService that acquires tokens for the BFF API using NAA,
    with proper caching and error handling.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      NAA is the Microsoft-recommended authentication pattern for Office Add-ins. It uses
      MSAL.js 3.x with createNestablePublicClientApplication() instead of the legacy
      createPublicClientApplication(). Tokens are acquired silently when possible,
      with interactive popup as fallback.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
